Replacing \$||\vec{C}||^2\$ with \$||\vec{B} - \vec{A}||^2\$ gives the following:

<div class="paragraph">
<p>\$||\vec{A}||^2 + ||\vec{B}||^2 - 2||\vec{A}||||\vec{B}||\cos\theta = ||\vec{B} - \vec{A}||^2\$</p>
